WEBVTT

00:33.072 --> 00:34.008
What?

00:34.108 --> 00:35.274
- We have pastelitos
in the oven.

00:35.374 --> 00:36.962
Another verse,
they might be flat.

00:37.062 --> 00:38.228
- Mm,
laugh now,

00:38.328 --> 00:39.878
but when I become rich
and famous,

00:39.978 --> 00:42.026
I want you to remember
this moment
and your lack of faith.

00:42.126 --> 00:44.596
- Who lacks faith?
Pay these when you hit it big.

00:44.696 --> 00:46.591
- Yeah.
You got the keys to the truck?

00:46.691 --> 00:48.126
- No, no, no, Daniel needs it
for the Connor wedding.

00:48.226 --> 00:50.144
- No, I'm making that delivery.

00:50.643 --> 00:51.847
- Pop, I told you.

00:51.947 --> 00:53.458
I'm taking Vanessa out
for our anniversary.

00:53.558 --> 00:56.758
- Mm, fourth anniversary.
Ask him where she's
making him go.

00:56.858 --> 00:58.139
Paolo's.

00:58.239 --> 01:00.057
Paolo's, the most expensive
place in Miami.

01:00.157 --> 01:01.822
Dinner there is like a weekend
at the Bahamas, right?

01:01.922 --> 01:03.740
- Vanessa Princessa, eh?

01:03.840 --> 01:06.234
She makes you take her
to dinners like this yet wonders
why you live at home.

01:06.334 --> 01:08.497
- Whoo!
- First of all,
she's not making me take her.

01:08.597 --> 01:10.953
Second, I live here because Mom
would have a heart attack

01:11.053 --> 01:12.449
if I moved out before
I was married.

01:12.549 --> 01:14.904
- You're getting married?
- No one is getting married.

01:15.004 --> 01:17.052
- Yeah, but you know
she's expecting a proposal
soon, right?

01:17.152 --> 01:19.738
Mom, that fan looks ridiculous.

01:19.838 --> 01:22.155
Besides, the AC's on fully.

01:22.255 --> 01:24.457
You know, who needs a fridge
when we can just leave
the milk out?

01:24.557 --> 01:25.684
It's only menopause.

01:25.784 --> 01:29.406
- I birth you,
I raise you,
I cook for you.

01:29.506 --> 01:31.424
I support every one

01:31.884 --> 01:34.700
I support every one
of your crazy dreams,
even this DJing thing,

01:34.800 --> 01:38.214
and in return when
my body's betraying me,
this is the thanks I get?

01:41.514 --> 01:42.948
- He's the one marrying
a lunatic.

01:43.048 --> 01:45.312
- I'm not getting married.
- They're right, Daniel.

01:45.887 --> 01:46.731
You can stick your head
in the sand,

01:46.808 --> 01:48.780
but a woman like Vanessa,

01:48.880 --> 01:50.161
pretty soon she's gonna
give you an ultimatum.

01:50.261 --> 01:51.619
- Now I have to hear it
from you too?

01:51.719 --> 01:52.961
- Well, I worry about you.

01:53.061 --> 01:54.573
- You are my little sister.

01:54.673 --> 01:55.839
It's my job to worry about you.

01:55.939 --> 01:57.373
- Natalie Garcia,

01:57.473 --> 01:58.662
what do you think you're doing
with that pricing gun?

01:58.739 --> 02:00.404
- Uh
- Is your homework done?

02:00.504 --> 02:03.128
- Yes.
- Calculus too?

02:03.228 --> 02:05.391
- Dad, give her a break.
She just wanted to help Mom.

02:05.491 --> 02:07.501
- She wants to help her mother,
she'll get into Princeton.

02:07.601 --> 02:09.687
We have already two idiotas
to take over the bakery.

02:09.788 --> 02:13.908
You are smart enough
to be President, eh?
Presidente.

02:14.008 --> 02:16.939
- Yo, how come she's always
the genius
and we're the idiotas?

02:17.039 --> 02:18.934
- This I ask myself every day.

02:19.034 --> 02:20.929
- Daniel, sing with me.
Everybody, sing with me.

02:24.865 --> 02:27.259
- I know you all think
Vanessa's a bit much,

02:27.359 --> 02:30.175
but she's driven, and that's one
of the things I love about her.

02:30.275 --> 02:32.208
She's smart, ambitious,
and yes,

02:32.308 --> 02:34.625
one day she might be my wife.

02:34.725 --> 02:36.543
But honestly,
tonight is just dinner.

02:37.679 --> 02:39.113
- Noa, over here!

02:39.213 --> 02:40.763
Did he cheat on you?
- Are you speaking to him?

02:40.863 --> 02:43.410
- Just when I think
you've hit rock bottom,
you start digging.

02:43.510 --> 02:46.249
- First up, the news breaking
the Internet today.

02:46.349 --> 02:49.702
Reports are Noa Hamilton,
the model turned fashion mogul,

02:49.802 --> 02:53.385
and Colin Davis,
the actor recently chosen
to be the next Batman,

02:53.485 --> 02:55.457
have broken up.
- Oh, my God.

02:55.557 --> 02:58.104
- This coming only days
after photos surface

02:58.204 --> 03:00.175
of Colin
getting a little too cozy

03:00.275 --> 03:02.669
with the costar of his most
recent film, "Red Line."

03:02.769 --> 03:04.741
- Ooh!
- What a jerk.

03:04.841 --> 03:06.352
- Aye, cry me a river.

03:06.452 --> 03:07.656
- But Ma
- Por favor.

03:07.756 --> 03:08.769
Her father's a billionaire.

03:08.869 --> 03:10.572
She never worked a hard day
in her life.

03:10.672 --> 03:12.912
- She started her own
fashion label when she was 16

03:13.012 --> 03:15.176
and her own cosmetics line
at 18.

03:15.276 --> 03:19.242
Plus, her YouTube channel,
50 million subscribers.

03:19.342 --> 03:20.777
I followed when there
were only 30.

03:20.877 --> 03:23.731
- Now, no comment from Noa
on the breakup just yet,

03:23.831 --> 03:28.450
but the Australian entrepreneur
was all smiles last night
at a fundraiser in New York.

03:30.276 --> 03:32.708
- That's exactly how
your mom looked the day we met.

03:57.591 --> 03:58.566
- In addition
to those selections,

03:58.666 --> 04:00.522
we have our
inspirational tasting

04:00.622 --> 04:03.591
where Paolo channels
his energies into a unique
dining experience for two.

04:03.691 --> 04:06.008
- That's $300 per person.

04:06.108 --> 04:08.425
- We'll do that.
- Give us a minute.

04:08.525 --> 04:10.343
- Yes, perhaps a minute.
Thank you.

04:14.203 --> 04:17.019
It's like a dream come true.

04:17.119 --> 04:19.358
- Happy anniversary.

04:19.459 --> 04:20.740
You look so handsome.

04:23.027 --> 04:24.308
So did you look
at the house I sent you?

04:24.408 --> 04:26.073
- Mm-hmm.
- And?

04:26.173 --> 04:27.991
- You're the expert.
- Okay.

04:28.091 --> 04:29.372
I know it doesn't seem
like a lot,

04:29.472 --> 04:30.983
but I've sold four homes
in that neighborhood this month.

04:31.083 --> 04:32.863
It's the next Little Haiti.
- Mm.

04:32.963 --> 04:35.395
- I know it's small
and I know it's a wreck,
but we can fix it up.

04:35.495 --> 04:38.196
Think about it.
A place of our own.

04:38.296 --> 04:40.383
For our future.

04:40.483 --> 04:42.186
It's even got room
for a nursery.

04:44.588 --> 04:46.176
- Have you decided?

04:46.276 --> 04:47.518
- Actually, could you direct me
to the restroom?

04:47.618 --> 04:48.861
- Right this way.

04:48.961 --> 04:50.242
- Be right back.

05:07.031 --> 05:10.292
Turn around.
Can't go with you staring.

05:14.435 --> 05:18.440
Mateo's right.
You heard her out there.

05:18.540 --> 05:22.238
Thing is, I feel like if I don't
propose soon, I'm screwed.

05:22.338 --> 05:24.908
At the same time I feel like
if I do propose soon,
I'm screwed.

05:26.596 --> 05:28.937
I must sound so crazy.

05:49.385 --> 05:51.510
- You know, if you have
to talk yourself into something,

05:51.610 --> 05:54.464
maybe you should
just stop talking.

05:54.564 --> 05:57.456
- Excuse me?

05:57.556 --> 05:59.566
- You didn't seem like you were
making a lot of headway.

06:02.122 --> 06:05.244
- Oh, you mean when I was on
the phone talking to my brother.

06:05.344 --> 06:08.030
- No, I mean when you were
talking to the picture
while you peed.

06:11.291 --> 06:13.109
- You should see what I do
in the shower.

06:13.209 --> 06:15.027
I hold conference calls
with the U.N.

06:15.127 --> 06:18.403
When I really want a challenge,
I'll do it in Japanese.

06:22.877 --> 06:24.541
- Oh, come on.

06:27.519 --> 06:32.138
- First time here?
Try the soup.
Everything else here sucks.

06:39.105 --> 06:40.654
- How's the soup?

06:40.754 --> 06:42.918
Daniel.
How's the soup?

06:43.018 --> 06:44.606
- It's good.
- Mm.

06:44.706 --> 06:48.596
